# Dashboard Sidebar Screenshot

## What to Capture
1. Open the Dashboard sidebar (View → vLLM-Copilot → Dashboard)
2. Expand one server node to show all metrics
3. Make sure the following are visible:
   - Server name with green/red status dot
   - Models subtree with model count
   - Context Window, KV Cache, KV Cache Hit
   - Avg TTFT, Throughput
   - Running, Waiting
   - MTP metrics (if active)

## Screenshot Tips
- Use VS Code's built-in screenshot or snipping tool
- Dark theme looks better in the README
- Crop to just the sidebar width (not full editor)
- Save as `dashboard-sidebar.png` in this folder